<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='80627' id='t-80627'>I can inject heat into the system here,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='83194' id='t-83194'>or I can pull it apart
with two of my fingers.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='85400' id='t-85400'>It's completely intuitive;
there's no instruction manual.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='88154' id='t-88154'>The interface just kind of disappears.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='90000' id='t-90000'>This started out as a screensaver app</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='91944' id='t-91944'>that one of the Ph.D. students
in our lab, Ilya Rosenberg, made.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='95015' id='t-95015'>But I think its true identity
comes out here.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 1:51
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='100153' id='t-100153'>Now what's great about a multi-touch
sensor is that, you know,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='103100' id='t-103100'>I could be doing this
with as many fingers here,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='105861' id='t-105861'>but of course multi-touch
